Receptionist cum Cashier
Al Ain Juniors School
Location:
Al Ain, Abu Dhabi
Date: 30-04-2014
Payrate: 3,000 To 3,500 Monthly (AED)
Job Type: Employee
Job Status: Full Time
Categories:
Secretarial
Customer Service
Al Ain Juniors School
Please see Job Details for Apply instructions
Saved!
Job Details
RESPONSIBILITIES
1.    General front-office responsibilities
Dealing with visitors/parents Greet parents and visitors and answer their inquiries about the school.Send support staff to escort parents and visitors to other relevant staff and management offices (of coordinators, VP, Principal, MD)fix appointments with parents, visitors if Vice Principal, Principal, MD, are not available at the time.Monitor entry and exit of visitors to and from the school premises.
Attending telephone calls Receive telephone calls, answer general inquiries about the school and specific inquiries such as admission inquiries, important school events, exams etc.Have up-to-date knowledge of and be able to clearly explain school policies and guidelines Remind Principal/MD to make return calls.Set appointments for parents and others with the Principal /MD, make follow up calls to parents and remind Principal / MD about the appointment Contact parents when their child becomes ill (upon the teacher's / coordinators’ request)Maintain confidentiality of reports, records, correspondence, and communications when required to handle such information
Typing work Type letters, memos, circulars etc. by MD, Principal, VP and Coordinators and type any other material requested by them Type requisition slips/order forms etc.Type orders for textbooks, uniforms, stationery, other supplies, etc
2.    Financial responsibilities
Receive fees and update accurate records in the software Receive payments for books, uniforms and other supplies for parents and students Transfer the collected fees to the authorized person on a daily basis Use care, safety and confidentiality in maintaining money and documents
3.    Administrative responsibilities
Ministry work: Maintain and update student admission, TC information on the software Keep accurate updated information on students profiles, admission, TC, fee payment, parent contact numbers
Type and issue Bonafide student certificates
Admission procedures Follow admission procedures with precision as instructed in the admission procedure manual Keep clear records of calls of admission requests, availability of seats, procurement of admission documents
Communicate day-to-day information to the concerned authorities – for eg. To Coordinators (for details of admissions), Operations Supervisor (for transport, etc.), Principals (for meeting with the parents, approval for admissions etc.), Accounts Supervisor (for fee matters), Arabic Secretaries (for admission of Arabic speaking students) etc.
Maintain individual files/documents for separate departments of the school.
